body:
@rakyll 
> We don't need to dynamically load an so. LGPL should be allowing us to dynamically link with an LGPL'ed shared library.

I thought he was suggesting dynamically loading a .so for easier (read: static-like) deployment.

@minux 
> It's a common misconception about LGPL that it forces you to use dynamic linking if your code is not under (L)GPL.

You are right, I had forgotten of this part.
